{"ts": "2026-06-08T23:47:13.797147+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here's a summary of how to run and build this React admin app locally and for different environments:\n\n---\n\n## How to Run Locally\n\n1. **Install dependencies** (uses Yarn):\n   ```bash\n   yarn\n   ```\n\n2. **Start the development server:**\n   ```bash\n   yarn dev\n   ```\n   - This runs Vite in dev mode with `NODE_ENV=local` (via `cross-env`), which loads the environment file at `envs/.env.local`.\n   - The dev server starts on **port 10086** with CORS enabled and host binding (`--host`), so it's accessible on your local network at `http://localhost:10086`.\n\n3. **Preview a production build locally:**\n   ```bash\n   yarn serve\n   ```\n   - This runs `vite preview --host`, serving the contents of the `dist/` folder (you need to build first).\n\n---\n\n## How to Build for Different Environments\n\nThe project uses **Vite's mode system** with per-environment `.env` files stored in the `envs/` directory. The Vite config (`vite.config.ts`) automatically loads the correct file based on the `NODE_ENV` environment variable:\n\n| Command | Script | Vite Mode | Env File Used | API Base URL |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `yarn build` | `vite build --mode prod` | `prod` | `envs/.env.prod` | `https://mock.prd.lantron.ltd` |\n| `yarn build:stg` | `cross-env vite build --mode test` | `test` | *(not found in repo — see note)* | — |\n| `yarn build:prod` | `cross-env vite build --mode production` | `production` | *(not found in repo — see note)* | — |\n| `yarn dev:stg` | `cross-env NODE_ENV=stg vite` | default | `envs/.env.stg` | `https://mock.stg.lantron.ltd` |\n\n**Available env files:**\n- `envs/.env.local` — local dev (`VITE_HOST=local.lantron.ltd`, port `10086`, mock API)\n- `envs/.env.stg` — staging (`VITE_HOST=stg.lantron.ltd`, port `10086`, staging mock API)\n- `envs/.env.prod` — production (`VITE_APP_BASE_API=https://mock.prd.lantron.ltd`)\n\n> **Note:** The `build:stg` and `build:prod` scripts use `--mode test` and `--mode production` respectively, but the Vite config resolves env files by `NODE_ENV`, not by Vite's `mode`. This means you may need to set `NODE_ENV` to `stg` or `prod` for those env files to load, or create `.env.test` / `.env.production` files in the `envs/` directory. The `build` script uses `--mode prod`, which matches `envs/.env.prod`.\n\nAll builds output to the **`dist/`** directory.\n\n---\n\n## Docker Deployment\n\nA multi-stage **Dockerfile** is provided:\n\n```bash\ndocker build -t vite-react-ts-admin .\ndocker run -p 80:80 vite-react-ts-admin\n```\n\n- **Stage 1 (builder):** Uses `node:lts-alpine`, runs `yarn` and `yarn build` to produce the `dist/` output.\n- **Stage 2 (runtime):** Uses `nginx:alpine`, copies `dist/` into nginx's html directory and a custom `nginx.conf` for SPA routing, then serves on **port 80**.\n\n---\n\n## Other Deployment Options\n\n- **GitHub Pages:** `yarn deploy` runs `gh-pages -d dist` to publish the `dist/` folder to GitHub Pages (homepage in package.json points to `https://reactZone.github.io/vite-react-ts-admin`).\n- **Netlify:** A `netlify.toml` is present (likely minimal config for SPA redirects).", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 912, "prompt_tokens": 11453, "total_tokens": 12365, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 17, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 11264, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0009162054, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0001227654, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00079344}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780962417-w0IYXwW7Koej2wgfgPu4", "finish_re